    "overview_title": "Circular Reasoning",
    "overview_subtitle": "Solving Area and Circumference Problems",
    "overview_description": "In this lesson, students recognize that when different figures have the same perimeter, the circle has the largest area. They use this concept to maximize area in a real-world situation, deriving a circleâ€™s area when given its circumference. Students calculate the area of composite figures and irregularly-shaped figures using addition or subtraction of areas."
