      "overview_item_title": "Essential Ideas",
      "overview_item_data": {
        "overview_item_data_type": "list",
        "overview_item_data_items": [
          "A circle has the largest area for a given perimeter.",
          "To calculate the area of a composite figure, divide it into familiar shapes, calculate the area of each of those shapes, then calculate the sum of those areas.",
          "To calculate the area of an irregularly shaped region, view it as a larger familiar shape with a smaller familiar shape as a hole in it. Calculate the difference of the areas of the two familiar shapes.",
          "You can use the circumference and area of a circle formulas to solve real-world problems."
